{%- comment -%}
  Added by DK on 2026-06-26: gender badge pill for product cards, sourced
  from Shopify's standard target-gender metafield. Renders alongside (not
  instead of) the existing product-card-badges pill, in its own position
  so it can coexist with the main badge (e.g. top-left badge + top-right
  gender pill). Position and visibility are controlled by the calling
  block's settings, not hardcoded, so it's switchable per-instance from
  the theme customizer. Markup/CSS structure mirrors product-card-badges.liquid.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Bracket notation required: Liquid dot notation can't parse a key
  containing a hyphen (target-gender). The metafield's .value is a list of
  shopify--target-gender metaobjects. Per Shopify's metaobject Liquid docs,
  each field on a metaobject is accessed as metaobject.<field_key>.value -
  so the "label" field needs its own .value, not just .label or
  .display_name as a bare property.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign gender_refs = product.metafields.shopify['target-gender'].value -%}
{%- assign gender = '' -%}
{%- if gender_refs != blank -%}
  {%- assign gender = gender_refs.first.label.value -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- if show_gender_badge and gender != blank -%}
  <div
    class="product-badges product-badges--{{ gender_badge_position }}"
    style="
      --badge-border-radius: {{ settings.badge_corner_radius }}px;
      --badge-font-family: var(--font-{{ settings.badge_font_family }}--family);
      --badge-font-weight: var(--font-{{ settings.badge_font_family }}--weight);
      --badge-text-transform: {{ settings.badge_text_transform }};
    "
  >
    <div class="product-badges__badge product-badges__badge--rectangle product-badges__badge--outline">
      {{ gender }}
    </div>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}

{% stylesheet %}
  .product-badges__badge--outline {
    background: var(--color-background);
    color: var(--color-foreground);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
{% endstylesheet %}
